RA sat on adm was 85 % , up to 91 % on 5 L NC. Plan is to get echo , empirically diurese . LEE is probably venous stasis : will get LENIs , then apply compression stockings if LENIs neg . This is a very difficult and demanding patient. 3 / 2 sats on 4L low 90s . Pt asking for tx for cellulitis , none seen clinically only longstanding venous stasis . EKG w / possible lat strain . 5 / 29 Pt is still not compliant w / cpap because her nose burns w / the oxygen despite humidification . Exam of nose is unremarkable . She is also refusing BP medication because she claims that she does not have high BP . She has an elevated wt ct and some pain and swelling of R LE. Will tx w / diclox for cellulitis . Pt recd flu shot and pneumovax . She says that she does not have a fever , cough or feels ill at this time . Pt suffered very minor trauma to Right first toe on her car . Examination is unremarkable . This can be followed up w / PCP . Dr . Pavoni ( her hematologist ) said that she is not a candidate for dvt prophylaxis second to bleeding ; she should not receive any anticoagulants unless strong clinical indication . ADDITIONAL COMMENTS : Please have appt w / Dr. Fridal and Dr. Trezza in one week . See Dr . Knipple at next available appt . Please have VNA for every other day to do respiratory eval and assistance w / medical care . Please have PT / OT to see pt twice weekly . Pt must use CPAP at 18 - 19 cm H2O for 8hrs night w / O2 at 4 - 5 L & w / ambulation . Sitz bath to vagina twice / d . Call your doctor if short of breath , chest pain , nausea / vomiting , worsening leg pain , headaches or other worrisome symptoms . Pt is to go to Emjeaneser / Valley Memorial Hospital as an outpatient . Home health aid twice per wk .
